<br>
I am *so* happy about this change.  This will not only give newer players something to 'look forward to' as far as items go, but will also bring some of the the challenge back to the lower level zones for those of us with 'twinked out' alts...  For a long time, those of us who came a little later to the party had literally nothing we could offer our friends and guildmates in our little lowbie adventuring groups/guilds but a good time, because folks would be handed items or toddle off to EC and be decked out by level 20 better than we could quest for them until 50...  It also ruined the economy for low/mid level players, because everything we did acquire in our adventures was, due to the 'trickle down' (or should I say avalanche) effect, by definition, 'junk'.  I really hope that this brings some of the joy and meaning back to those low level raids/quests for what are really some very nice items for the level. <br>
<br>
